#: ../../F/frob.rst:5
msgid "frob"
msgstr "frob"

#: ../../F/frob.rst:7
msgid "/frob/"
msgstr "/frob/"

#: ../../F/frob.rst:9
msgid ""
"n\\. [MIT; very common] The :ref:`TMRC` definition was \"FROB = a protruding"
" arm or trunnion\"; by metaphoric extension, a frob is any random small "
"thing; an object that you can comfortably hold in one hand; something you "
"can frob (sense 2). See :ref:`frobnitz`\\."
msgstr ""
"名詞 [MIT。非常に一般的]\\ :ref:`TMRC`\\ の定義は「FROB = "
"突き出した腕またはトラニオン」だった。比喩的な拡張により、frobとは任意の小さなもの、片手で楽に持てる物体、frob(語義2)できるものをいう。\\ "
":ref:`frobnitz`\\ を参照。"

#: ../../F/frob.rst:13
msgid "vt\\. Abbreviated form of :ref:`frobnicate`\\."
msgstr "他動詞 \\ :ref:`frobnicate`\\ の省略形。"

#: ../../F/frob.rst:17
msgid ""
"[from the :ref:`MUD` world] A command on some MUDs that changes a player's "
"experience level (this can be used to make wizards); also, to request "
":ref:`wizard` privileges on the ‘professional courtesy’ grounds that one is "
"a wizard elsewhere. The command is actually ‘frobnicate’ but is universally "
"abbreviated to the shorter form."
msgstr ""
"[\\ :ref:`MUD`\\ "
"の世界から]一部のMUDで、プレイヤーの経験値レベルを変えるコマンド(これはウィザードを作るのに使える)。また、自分はよそではウィザードだという‘職業上の礼儀’を根拠に、\\"
" :ref:`wizard`\\ 権限を要求すること。コマンドは実際には‘frobnicate’だが、普遍的により短い形に省略される。"
